public abstract class AbstractUrlShortener
extends Object
implements UrlShortener

A partial UrlShortener implementation.

The typical UrlShortener works by talking to a server. The URL to be shortened is passed to the server, often as part of a query string. The shortened URL is then parsed from the server response.

Aside from the specifics of the request URL used to communicate to the server and the format of the response, the above is very similar among many URL shortening APIs. This class performs the common steps, so implementations need only provide getRequestUrl(String) and parseServerResponse(CharSequence). (Services with a text-only response might even be able to make do with the default parseServerResponse(CharSequence)).

Author:
Miorel-Lucian Palii
